## 🟠 Application 4: POS App

### Modules Reviewed
`auth` · `cart` · `checkout` · `draft_billing` · [pos](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/admin/lib/features/inventory/view/add_product_view.dart#120-132) · `products` · `reports` · `sales` · `settings` · `shared_cart`

### Bugs & Errors

| # | Severity | File | Issue |
|---|----------|------|-------|
| 1 | 🔴🔴 **CRITICAL** | [login_view.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/features/auth/view/login_view.dart#L56) | **PLAINTEXT PASSWORD COMPARISON** — Line 56: `userResponse['password'] != password`. Passwords are stored in plaintext in the `employees` table and compared directly. This is a **severe security vulnerability**. All passwords are exposed if the database is compromised. Must use bcrypt/argon2 hashing. |
| 2 | 🔴 Critical | [login_view.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/features/auth/view/login_view.dart#L33-L34) | **Duplicate `_errorMessage` assignment** — Lines 33-34 both set `_errorMessage`, with line 34 overwriting line 33. Dead code. |
| 3 | 🔴 Critical | [login_view.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/features/auth/view/login_view.dart#L151-L152) | **Duplicate `labelText` property** — Lines 151-152 both set `labelText` on the same `InputDecoration`. Line 152 silently overwrites line 151. This is a Dart compile warning. |
| 4 | 🔴 Critical | [main.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/main.dart#L24-L27) | **Hardcoded Supabase credentials** — URL and anon key directly in [main()](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/admin/lib/main.dart#15-41) with no `.env` file usage at all. |
| 5 | 🟡 Medium | [main.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/main.dart#L220-L234) | **Session management via SharedPreferences only** — POS session is stored as a `pos_device_id` string in SharedPreferences. No Supabase auth session. A stolen device with cleared login but cached prefs gives access. |
| 6 | 🟡 Medium | [login_view.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/features/auth/view/login_view.dart#L42-L46) | **SQL injection risk** — Employee lookup uses string interpolation in `.or()` filter: `'login_id.eq."$loginId",mobile.eq."$loginId"'`. While Supabase client SDK generally parameterizes queries, this pattern is fragile. |
| 7 | 🟡 Medium | [main.dart](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/pos/lib/main.dart#L53) | **Duplicate comment** — `// 2. Determine Effective Theme` appears twice (lines 52-53). |

### UI/UX Issues

| # | Issue |
|---|-------|
| 1 | Login uses [TextField](file:///Users/srinivasanp/Zenthink/Projects/pharmacy_management/apps/admin/lib/features/inventory/view/add_product_view.dart#1256-1286) instead of `TextFormField` — no form validation framework |
| 2 | Error messages show raw exception text (`Connection Error: $e`) to end users |
| 3 | No "Forgot Password" or any password recovery mechanism |
| 4 | No logout button visible — unclear how employees sign out |
| 5 | POS doesn't use GoRouter — entire app uses `Navigator.pushReplacement`. Loses consistent navigation |

### Missing Validations

| # | Issue |
|---|-------|
| 1 | No password hashing — stored and compared in plaintext |
| 2 | No login attempt rate limiting |
| 3 | No session expiry — once logged in via SharedPreferences, session persists indefinitely |
| 4 | No role/permission check — any employee can access full POS regardless of role |
| 5 | Employee ID field accepts any text with no format validation |

### Suggested Enhancements

- **URGENT**: Implement password hashing (bcrypt via Supabase Edge Function or server-side)
- Use Supabase Auth instead of custom employees table authentication
- Add session timeout for POS terminals
- Add role-based access control per employee
- Add terminal lock screen (for employee shift changes)
- Implement audit trail for all POS transactions

